OL,3,CCuba hit by third nationwide blackout
OL,4,Cthis month amid US energy blockade
OL,6,FOn Monday, as Cuba endured a
OL,7,Fnationwide blackout, Trump, alongside
OL,8,FRubio in the Oval Office, declared: "I
OL,9,Fdo believe I'll be having the honour
OL,10,Fof taking Cuba. It's a big honour, I
OL,11,Fmean, whether I free it, take it. I
OL,12,Fthink I can do anything I want with
OL,13,Fit."
OL,15,FRubio appeared to confirm earlier
OL,16,Freports in The Miami Herald and The
OL,17,FNew York Times that the administration
OL,18,Fwas demanding that Diaz-Canel and
OL,19,Fother officials viewed as obstacles to
OL,20,Freform step down.
OL,26,@pD@eOUuD@DO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1774303863
OL,3,CCuba hit by third nationwide blackout
OL,4,Cthis month amid US energy blockade
OL,6,F"The people in charge, they don't know
OL,7,Fhow to fix (Cuba's economy)," Rubio
OL,8,Fsaid. "So they have to get new people
OL,9,Fin charge. That's what has to happen."
OL,11,FTrump mused as well about Cuba's
OL,12,F"great weather" while bizarrely and
OL,13,Ffalsely asserting that the island,
OL,14,Fjust 90 miles from Florida, is "not in
OL,15,Fthe hurricane zone".
OL,17,FThe comments played into the hands of
OL,18,FCuba's hardliners who have long
OL,19,Fclaimed the ultimate goal of the US is
OL,20,Fto annex their island.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@]O]pD@GOUqD@fO]tD@AOUtD@OO]vD@
OL,26,A`OUwD@SO]
