OL,3,CCuba hit by third nationwide blackout
OL,4,Cthis month amid US energy blockade
OL,6,FDespite the rising tensions and
OL,7,FTrump's belligerent comments, Cuban
OL,8,Fofficials said they would continue
OL,9,Fwith negotiations.
OL,11,F"We will also be open to a serious and
OL,12,Fresponsible dialogue with the
OL,13,Fgovernment of the United States,
OL,14,Fwithout interference in internal
OL,15,Faffairs or in our respective
OL,16,Fpolitical, economic, and social
OL,17,Fsystems," Foreign Minister Bruno
OL,18,FRodriguez Parrilla said Saturday at a
OL,19,Fforum for Latin American, Caribbean
OL,20,Fand African countries.
OL,26,@sD@AOUyD@IO]zD@Ert
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/13
